summary:
I'm a policy specialist with 8 years of combined experience in the non-profit, community, government and corporate sectors developing, implementing and evaluating high impact projects, programs, materials, events, and creative and academic content. I have worked on cross-sector environmental educational and policy programs alongside major actors such as the City of Vancouver, the Municipality of North Cowichan, the British Columbian Teachers Federation of America, and Waste Management. 

Until recently, I led Customer Care (UK) at rapid growth international e-commerce startup providing 21st century booking service for the moving industry. In this role I was focused on B2B and B2C communication care, which included developing and testing standard operating procedure and training staff while managing a high case load. 

Colleagues and collaborators know me as a highly impactfull communicator whose creative and strategic insights are trusted in propelling forward meaningful ideas, projects, and proposals. with creative marketer who can always be trusted to come up with a new approach. As a trained facilitator and enthusiastic networker, I grow impact through the relationships I build. Be it through thoughtful feedback or comprehensive research, I draw upon 8 years of social scientific study to help executives, managers, and stakeholders transform obstacles into opportunities. 

I have an MA from the University of Victoria and a BA from Wilfred Laurier University.

I currently freelancing while testing Socialogic Solutions, a social venture that specializes in the generation, acceleration and evaluation of environmental and social impact projects. I am currently entertaining investment interest in this prototype. 

Please contact socialogicsolutions@gmail.com for more info.
